<h2>Finding 1: AI Overviews Trigger on 25.8% of All US Searches</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Google launched AI Overviews to 1 billion users in 2024. The feature generates AI summaries at the top of search results, pushing organic listings below the fold.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> As of January 2026, AI Overviews appear on 25.8% of all US searches. That figure represents a 58% increase from late 2024. Informational queries trigger <a href="/glossary/ai-overviews/">AI Overviews</a> at an even higher rate: 39.4% of the time.</p>
<p><strong>Context:</strong> The rollout has not been steady. AI Overview visibility peaked at nearly 25% in July 2025, then fell below 16% by November 2025 as Google pulled back on quality issues. By Q1 2026, visibility surged past the previous peak. This volatility makes planning difficult for businesses that depend on <a href="/blog/increase-organic-traffic/">organic search traffic</a>.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="AI Overviews trigger rate growth from 2024 to Q1 2026" src="/images/blog/ai-overviews-trigger-rate-growth.webp" /></p>
<h2>Finding 2: Only 7.9% of Local Searches Triggered AI Overviews. But That Is Changing Fast</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Local search queries like "plumber near me" or "best pizza downtown" have historically triggered map packs and local 3-packs. AI Overviews were expected to stay focused on informational queries.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> In late 2025, only 7.9% of local searches triggered an AI Overview. That number understates the real disruption. Restaurant queries jumped from a 10% trigger rate to 78%. Education-related local queries went from 18% to 83%. B2B tech local queries climbed from 36% to 82%.</p>
<p><strong>Context:</strong> The 7.9% average masks industry-specific surges. If you run a restaurant, tutoring center, or IT services company, AI Overviews already dominate your search results. Service businesses in plumbing, HVAC, and <a href="/blog/electrician-seo-guide/">electrical work</a> still see lower trigger rates. That gap will close. Google has expanded AI Overviews to every major query category within 18 months of launch.</p>
