<p>The pattern is clear. Google tests AI Overviews in one industry, refines the format, then expands to the next. Businesses in currently low-trigger industries should prepare now. The window to build content authority before AI Overviews dominate your category is closing. Track your industry trigger rates monthly through tools like <a href="https://www.semrush.com/blog/ai-seo-statistics/">Semrush</a> or manual SERP checks.</p>
<h2>Finding 3: AI Local Packs Show 68% Fewer Businesses</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> The traditional <a href="/glossary/local-pack/">local pack</a> displays 3 businesses with their name, rating, address, and a call button. This format has driven local discovery for over a decade.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> AI local packs display only 32% as many unique businesses as traditional packs. That means 68% fewer businesses get any visibility. Most AI local packs show just 1 or 2 businesses instead of 3. Call buttons are absent from the AI format.</p>
<p><strong>Context:</strong> Fewer slots create a winner-take-all dynamic. The businesses that appear in the AI local pack capture a disproportionate share of attention. Businesses excluded from the AI pack lose visibility entirely for that query. This makes <a href="/glossary/gbp-optimization/">Google Business Profile optimization</a> more critical than ever. A complete, well-reviewed profile is no longer enough. Content authority and topical relevance now influence which businesses the AI selects.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="AI local pack vs traditional local pack comparison" src="/images/blog/ai-local-pack-vs-traditional.webp" /></p>
<h2>Finding 4: 88% of Local Markets Lost Business Visibility</h2>
<p><strong>Background:</strong> Sterling Sky analyzed 322 local markets across the United States to measure the impact of AI local packs on business visibility.</p>
<p><strong>Results:</strong> 88% of those markets showed fewer unique businesses in AI packs compared to standard <a href="/glossary/map-pack/">map pack</a> listings. Some businesses reported 50% or greater declines in visibility. The reduction affected every business category tracked.</p>
<p><strong>Context:</strong> This is not a temporary glitch. Google is testing and expanding AI local packs on approximately 7% of tracked keywords as of early 2026. At the current pace, most high-intent local queries could return AI pack results within 12 to 18 months. Businesses that rely on the traditional 3-pack for discovery need a new strategy. Multi-location presence, <a href="/blog/nap-consistency/">strong NAP consistency</a>, and content-driven authority are the factors that determine AI pack inclusion.</p>
