<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>How do AI Overviews affect local business visibility?</strong></p>
<p>AI Overviews push organic results below the fold and reduce click-through rates by up to 58%. AI local packs show 68% fewer businesses than traditional 3-packs. Businesses not cited in the AI summary lose visibility entirely for that query. The effect varies by industry, with restaurants and education seeing the highest disruption.</p>
<p><strong>Do AI Overviews appear for "near me" searches?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, but at lower rates than informational queries. Only 7.9% of local searches triggered AI Overviews in late 2025. That rate is climbing rapidly in specific industries. Restaurant queries now trigger AI Overviews 78% of the time. Service-based queries like "plumber near me" still trigger traditional local packs more often.</p>
<p><strong>Can local businesses benefit from AI Overviews?</strong></p>
<p>Yes. Businesses cited inside AI Overviews earn 35% higher organic CTR than non-cited competitors. The key is producing content that Google AI considers citation-worthy: detailed guides, accurate business information, strong reviews, and <a href="/blog/structured-data-guide/">proper schema markup</a>. Getting cited turns the AI Overview from a threat into a traffic driver.</p>
<p><strong>What is the difference between AI local packs and traditional local packs?</strong></p>
<p>Traditional local packs show 3 businesses with ratings, addresses, and call buttons. AI local packs show 1 to 2 businesses without call buttons. AI packs weight content authority and topical relevance more than proximity. Traditional packs weight proximity, reviews, and <a href="/blog/improve-google-maps-ranking/">GBP completeness</a> more heavily.</p>
<p><strong>How fast are AI Overviews expanding in local search?</strong></p>
<p>AI local packs appear on approximately 7% of tracked keywords as of early 2026. Industry-specific trigger rates grew by 100% to 680% in 12 months. At the current pace, most high-intent local queries could display AI pack results within 12 to 18 months. The expansion is not linear. Google tests aggressively, then pulls back, then expands again.</p>
<p><strong>Should local businesses invest in ads because of AI Overviews?</strong></p>
<p>Ad investment is one response, but not the only one. Local pack ads grew from 1% to 22% of mobile results in 12 months. LSAs appear on 31% of queries. Ads deliver immediate visibility but stop working when the budget stops. A balanced approach combines GBP optimization, content publishing, and selective ad spend on high-intent queries.</p>
<p>AI Overviews are not replacing local search. They are reshaping how Google displays and filters local results. The businesses that earn AI citations will capture more visibility than they had before. The businesses that ignore this shift will watch their organic traffic decline quarter over quarter. Start optimizing now.</p>
